Looking for the ultimate three-day weekend road trip? Look no further than the City by the Bay! San Francisco's perfect location makes it the ideal starting point for an unforgettable adventure to so many incredible wonders. Some of the most notable being: Yosemite, Kings Canyon, and Sequoia National Parks. 🚐🗺️

At approximately four hours of drive time, you could be in Yosemite before lunch! Either spend the weekend exploring the seemingly endless trails through the valley, or for those with more time to explore, head south to marvel at the giant trees in Kings Canyon and Sqeuoia.

Make the most of a weekender by embarking on this unforgettable road trip from San Francisco. Tag along with us using #MoterraMoments as you venture into the wilderness, and let us know which park stole your heart. 📷❤️

Spent 2 weeks road tripping the PNW with @moterra 🚐 

Highly recommend booking a trip with them. Such a fun way to explore.

We know the spectacle of fireworks 🎆 on the 4th of July is a must for most, so we thought it would be helpful to put together a list of the best places to view the festivities in each of our locations. 

1.) 🦞 Maine: Portland's Eastern Promenade offers a fantastic view of the fireworks over Casco Bay. Another great option is Bar Harbour, ME, where you can enjoy the fireworks right over Frenchman Bay.

2.) 🌲 Washington: Gas Works Park in Seattle provides a stunning backdrop of the city skyline and Lake Union for the Fourth of July fireworks.

3.) 🏜️ Utah: Liberty Park in Salt Lake City hosts an annual fireworks show with live music, food trucks, and a festive atmosphere.

4.) 🏜️ Nevada: In Las Vegas, the Strip is the place to be for an unforgettable fireworks show. The famous hotels and casinos along Las Vegas Boulevard put on a dazzling display that lights up the entire city.

5.) 🌊 California: San Francisco's Pier 39 offers a prime viewing location for the fireworks over the bay. 

6.) 🗻 Montana: Whitefish's Whitefish Lake has an annual dazzling display of fireworks illuminating the night sky over the pristine waters of Whitefish Lake in Montana.

7.) 🏔️ Wyoming: Jackson Hole's Town Square is a popular gathering place for locals and visitors to watch the fireworks. Enjoy the show with the stunning Teton Mountains as a backdrop. Arguably the best option, however, is at  Phil Beaux Park at the base of Snow King Mtn resort. Join the locals for food trucks, live music, and one of the most incredible fireworks shows in the West!

Are you a craft beer expert or a beer lover in general? 🍻🌟
Discover Portland, ME's Beer Scene! 🍻🌆

Don't miss out on the vibrant beer industry in Maine's most populous city, which has become an integral part of it's charm. Just like picking a favorite van layout, choosing a favorite brewery can be tough. So, we'll guide you to two happening areas where you can get a taste of them all, and decide for yourself!

📍 East Bayside Breweries: As you enter the city (exit 7 off of 295), keep an eye out for the charming neighborhood of East Bayside on your left. It's home to a handful of excellent breweries. Start your journey at @austinstreetbrewery or @risingtidebeer, conveniently located in the same parking lot, where live music and food trucks often enhance the experience. These breweries are also just a two-minute drive from Whole Foods and Trader Joe's. From there, take a quick five-minute walk to discover trendy spots like @apresdrinks (a hard seltzer bar), @belleflowerbeer, @lonepinebrewing, @Fermentory, and @bluelobsterwines. There's something for everyone!

📍 Riverton Breweries: Tucked away in the neighborhood of Riverton (ten minutes from downtown Portland), you'll find a former industrial park transformed into a beer enthusiast's paradise. Start your visit at @allagashbrewing, renowned for their widely distributed Allagash White and outstanding Belgian-style ales. Treat yourself to a lobster roll from their permanent food truck, and then stroll right across the street to explore the offerings of @definitivebrewing, @foundationbrew (don't miss the Epiphany - it lives up to its name), and @batterysteelebrewing.
Conveniently, this bustling cluster of businesses is located next door to @hannafordmkts the local supermarket - get two birds with one stone!

No matter your preference for beer, you're sure to find something worth bringing home to your fridge. 🍻

🍁 The east coast boasts an impressive array of activities and things to see during the world-famous phenomenon of the changing season. Three states specifically grab our attention, and we thought it would be advantageous to share the inside scoop on some can't-miss adventures in three of our favorite destinations: New Hampshire, Maine, and Vermont.

🏔️ New Hampshire: Take a scenic drive along the Kancamagus Highway in the White Mountains, where you'll be surrounded by breathtaking fall foliage. 🍁 Stop for a hike or check out viewpoints along the way to fully experience the beauty of the season.

🌳 Maine: Explore Acadia National Park during the fall season and witness the vibrant colors of the changing leaves. 🍂 Hike the trails, 🚲 bike along the carriage roads, and enjoy the picturesque views of the Atlantic Ocean from the park's grand overlooks.

🍂 Vermont: Visit Stowe, Vermont, known for its stunning fall foliage. Take a gondola ride to the top of Mount Mansfield for panoramic views, or indulge in local farm-to-table cuisine. Don't miss the iconic covered bridges and quaint country towns that epitomize the charm of Vermont in the fall. 🌻

We are absolutely devastated to hear about the passing of Jimmy Buffett. On one of our first visits to the @fieldvans production facility in California, the owner shared with us that they had built him a custom van in that same space! When we shared what big fans we were, he dug up and gifted us custom pins that Jimmy had made to celebrate his new 'land sailboat.'

Jimmy's music set the stage for every childhood summer BBQ, family camping trip and even a few tropical Christmas'. His songs inspired towards wanderlust, following our joy, music, entrepreneurship and knowing that through these changes in latitudes, changes in attitudes, if we didn't laugh we would all go insane. @jimmybuffett thank you for being such a force of positivity. Must Do Fall Roadtrip in Banff 🚙🍁
With @moterra 

I road-tripped to Banff for the first time in September 2021 when the borders had just opened again. My friend and I tent camped because it was so last minute, and with the temps, it wasn’t ideal haha. So glad we had the van this time especially with Alana! 

Day 1: 
-pick up @moterra van at their whitefish location (or you could pick up in salt lake and do round trip if you live nearby) 
-drive the 5 hours to Banff and catch sunset at Vermillion Lakes
-stay the night at Lake Louise Campground 

Day 2:
-wake up early and catch sunrise at Lake Louise and hike to Little Beehive and the tea house
-make a late breakfast at the van back in the parking lot and enjoy some coffee by the lake 
-walk downtown Banff in the afternoon and grab some lunch at @roseandcrownbanff 
-make dinner at the campsite and relax by the fire before another early morning 

Day 3:
-wake up super early and head to the shuttle pick up for Moraine Lake (I’ll post a reel specifically on how to visit if you are interested!) @morainelakebus 
-catch sunrise at the rock pile at Moraine Lake and start off for Larch Valley 
-ride the shuttle down and make lunch and maybe a nap in the van before heading off for Jasper 
-drive the beautiful Icefield parkway to Jasper and stop at any of the countless beautiful lakes and overlooks 
-make dinner and relax at camp in Wapiti Campground 

Day 4:
-make some breakfast in the van and then head off back to Canmore, stopping at any of the additional spots such as Peyto Lake
-arrive in Canmore and explore downtown and grab dinner at @thegrizzlypaw 

If you want a more in depth/longer itinerary check out the link in my bio! 

Follow me @adventurewithanna_ for more Utah and family travel content ✨

We spent the last week in a @moterra campervan while climbing in Red Rock, and it was amazing! 🚐

Our friend @brian.m.hackworth was visiting and so we rented a second van so that we would all have a place to sleep inside and have an indoor kitchen and space to hang out in since sunset is so early now. 

The @moterra high roof van that we were in (Shuksan model) had everything we needed for a very comfortable camping experience. My favorite was having a hot shower after climbing, but the kitchen was also wonderful and well stocked and the bed was huge and comfy! 

We camped at the Red Rock Canyon Campground, which is across the street from a ton of climbing. Red Rock is one of my favorite climbing areas and we did a mix of sport, trad, and bouldering, but there’s also a lot of hiking in the area as well. 

If you’re looking to try out vanlife, or want to road trip in a van, check out Moterra. They have a location in Vegas which is the perfect hub for trips to Red Rock, Valley of Fire, Death Valley, and Zion!

And Seattle locals, they even have a location near you!

Oregon road trip: Part 1 with @moterra campervan 🚐 

A couple weeks ago I partnered with @moterra on a 5 day road trip from Seattle, WA to San Francisco, CA. Here’s Part 1 of my adventure!

📍 Astoria, OR - many famous spots where the classic 80s movie, the Goonies was filmed!
📍 Portland and Mt. Hood, OR - discovered some amazing fall hikes and waterfalls 
📍 Bend, OR - stopped at the Last Blockbuster 🎥 on the PLANET 🌍 and explored some amazing craft breweries 

Found a dispersed camping spot using @thedyrt outside of the famous Crater Lake

Follow along for Part 2 of this epic jam packed road trip to catch the Oregon Coast and find some cool spots on the way to San Francisco!

Part 2 of @moterra campervans road trip from Oregon to San Francisco, CA.

📍 Umpqua National Forest, OR - underrated national forest! Epic waterfall hikes and the scenic byway is amazing!

📍 Thors Well, OR - Also known as the drainpipe of the Pacific, the well is actually a hole in the rock that only appears to drain water from the ocean.

📍 Avenue of the Giants - a scenic highway in northern California, United States, running through Humboldt Redwoods State Park. It is named after the coastal redwoods that tower over the route. 

🏖️ 🥾 Point Reyes National Seashore hike

🌁 Final stop at Golden Gate Bridge 

Overall amazing experience with @moterra and recommend to anyone who is looking to try out the van life!

A week in a @moterra campervan ⤵️

While we were in Las Vegas, we were hosted in a Moterra van and it was such an amazing experience! The van had a hot indoor shower, a full (van sized) kitchen, and everything we needed for a week of camping. Our friend Brian was visiting us for climbing, and this van was perfect for chilly nights so we could all cook and hang out inside. 

🚐 We camped at the Red Rock Canyon campground the entire week. We always prefer camping when we’re climbing in Vegas because it’s so much closer and avoids the hustle and bustle of downtown. 

🧗🏻‍♀️ The whole week we climbed at Red Rock, both in and out of the park. And we did a mix of sport, trad, multipitch, bouldering, and even a hike after it had rained. 

If you’re looking to rent a camper an on your next trip, make sure to check out @moterra
